    <note>Xu(3) Renjie [757] Jiangxi TZ, 10.3b-4a, 22.6b; Han Yuanji, WJ, 22.31b-33b (2nd wife, surname Lu(1), who was also married before. She married her first husband, Zhou(1) Zhicai(2) [16506], at age 17 and had three children by him, one son and two daughters. She was the mother of Renjie's third son, Wenqing [16505] (q.v.), and one daughter. Her immediate patrilineal ancestors were all classicists (ruye), who held no office, but her elder cousin, Xiang [16509], held office, had literary fame, and made the lineage illustrious (zhuxing) in Quzhou. Her grandsons (sons of Wenqing, or of Zhou(1) Zhicai(2)'s son ?) have the same generational indicator in their mingzi as Lu(1) Xiang!). Xiang may be the same person as the Quxian county resident, Jingwen (name not included in dataset), who earned the jinshi in 1124. The 1076 Yushan jinshi, Xu(3) Fu [752] and Xu(3) Ke [18590], were probably grandfather or granduncle, but there are no extant documentary links, therefore they are designated as belonging to a separate lineage. CBD, 3, 2015. See 安人盧氏墓誌銘（南澗甲乙稿22/28）.</note>
